Title: Many-body Dynamics of D0--Branes
Authors: H. Awata, S. Chaudhuri, M. Li, and D. Minic
Comments: 9 pages, latex, minor changes
Report-no: EFI-97-27
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D57 (1998) 5303-5306
\\
  We show that the growth of the size with the number of partons holds in a
Thomas-Fermi analysis of the threshold bound state of D0--branes. Our results
sharpen the evidence that for a fixed value of the eleven dimensional radius
the partonic velocities can be made arbitrarily small as one approaches the
large N limit.
